<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-06-08T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-06-08T16:00:00-05:00" n="862" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d862">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 341.622a/150a</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PWH1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Page</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-06-08T16:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">June 8, 1916, 4 p. m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>3402. Your 4335<note n="1" xml:id="d862fn1">
                                <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_646">p.
                                646</ref>.</note> May 20. Please take up the <hi rend="italic">China</hi> case again with <persName corresp="#p_GSE1">Sir Edward
                                Grey</persName>, and tell him that I am anxious to know at the
                            earliest moment when the persons will be released and what arrangements
                            are being made for their transportation to their destination, as
                            indicated in your note to him. Nearly three weeks have now elapsed
                            without any reply and I can not allow the settlement of this important
                            case to be unduly delayed.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>